name: Bristles - The Gnomes on the Bus Go...
description:
Hidden in the bush in the Ferguson Valley in Western Australia’s South West lies Gnomesville, a quirky collection of around 10000 garden gnomes placed into their own little community by visitors. This small group of gnomes cluster around their own custom built school bus.

Original photography filtered through the lens of generative abstraction. Digital oil painted onto a noisy geometric canvas. 6000x6000. Made in Processing.
